When three dice are rolled together, what is the probability of getting the sum as 10?

 (A)1/ 36           (B)1/ 6           (C)1/ 8                         (D)1/ 9

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details:
When three dice are rolled, the total number of possibilities are 6^3 = 216  the possible cases

for the sum to be 10 are (1,3,6)= 3!= 6, (1,4,5)= 6   ,(2,2,6)= 3, (2,3,5)= 6, (2,4,4)= 3 , ( 3,4,3)= 3  Total= 27 27/216= 1/8

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: If two dice are rolled, the total number of possibilities is n(s) = 36. The possible cases for the sum to be 9 are {(3, 6), (4, 5), (6, 3), (5, 4)}. i.e. 4. ∴ Required probability = 4/ 36= 1/9

questionContent.body:
The probability of getting at least 4 tails when 6 coins are tossed is

 (A  3/4           (B) 15/ 16     (C)  7/16         (D)  11/32

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details:
When n coins are tossed, the probability of getting ‘r’ heads is nC r / 2^n

Probability of getting at least 4 tails = P(4 tails) + P (5

tails) + P (6 tails) = 6C4/2^6+ 6C5/2^ 6+ 

6C6/2^6 =(15+ 6+1)/ 64 = 11/32

questionContent.body:
A coin is tossed 10 times. Find the probability of obtaining heads at least once.

 (A)1/(2^10)    (B) 10/ (2^10)                       (C) 9/ (2^10)               (D) (2^10-1)/2^10

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details:
Let E be the event of heads occurring at least once and E! be the event of heads not occurring at all i.e., all tails. P(E) = 1-P(E! )

1-  1 / 2 ^10= (2^10-1)/2^10

A girl walking at the speed of 3 km/hr covers a certain distance in 9 hours 30 minutes. If she covers the same

distance by cycle in 8 hours, then what is the speed (in km/hr) of cycle?

A) 2.5                    B) 4                        C) 3                        D) None of these

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Hint  Distance = Speed × Time Distance covered by the girl = 3 km/hr × 9.5 hours = 28.5 km. The cycle covers the same distance in 8 hours. Speed of cycle = Distance / Time = 28.5 km / 8 hours = 3.5625 km/hr.

questionContent.body:
Sunil started his journey at 2:33:34 p.m. and reached the destination at 4:43:45p.m. Anil started the journey 45 min 27 secs after Sunil and reached the destination 37 mins 16 secs after him. How long did Anil take to complete his journey?

A) 5 hour 59 mins            B) 3 hours 2 mins      C) 7 hours   D) None of these

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details:
Hint Sunil's journey duration is the difference between his end time (4:43:45 p.m.) and start time (2:33:34 p.m.), which is 2 hours, 10 minutes, and 11 seconds. Anil's journey was shorter than

Sunil's by the difference between when he started and when he reached, which is

(45 min 27 s)−(37 min 16 s)=8 min 11 s. Therefore, Anil's total journey time is

(2 h 10 min 11 s)−(8 min 11 s). This calculation results in 2 hours and 2 minutes.

questionContent.body:
A mini-van crosses two people walking at the speed of 4.8 kmph and 6 kmph in the same direction as that in which the mini-van is heading in 4.5 s and 9 s, respectively. What is the length of the mini-van?

A) 3.5 m               B) 3 m                   C) 4 m                   D) None of these

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Hint Let the length of the mini-van be L and its speed be V. The relative speeds are (V−4.8) kmph and (V−6) kmph. Using the formula L=relative speed×time, we have (V−4.8)×4.5=(V−6)×9. Solving for V, we find V=7.2 kmph. The length L is then (7.2−4.8)× 5/18 ​ × 4.5 = 2.4× 5/18 ​ × 4.5 = 3 m.

questionContent.body:
A can do a work in 15 days and B in 9 days. If they work on it together for 5 days, then what fraction of work is left?

A) 1/6                   B) 3/7                   C) 1/3                   D) None of these

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Hint Total Work: LCM of 15 and 9 = 45 units. A's Rate: 45/15=3 units/day. B's Rate: 45/9=5 units/day. Combined Rate: 3+5=8 units/day. Work completed in 5 days: 8×5=40 units. Work left: 45−40=5 units. Fraction of work left: Work left : Total work ​ = 5:45 ​ =1:9

1410x/12x = 235/2

solution.details:
Work done by the third pipe in 1 min = 1/50 - (1/60 + 1/75) = - 1/100. [-ve sign means emptying]

The third pipe alone can empty the cistern in 100 min.

questionContent.body:
Ramesh bought two boxes for Rs. 1300. He sold one box at a profit of 20% and the other box at a loss of 12%. If the selling price of both boxes is the same, Find the cost price of each box.      

A. 650,650      B. 550,750      C. 450,850                  D. None of these

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details:
Since Profit% is 20; CP1 = 5, SP1 = 6

Since Loss% is 12; CP2 = 25, SP2 = 22

Since Selling price of both are equal, SP1 = SP2 = 66 So, CP1 = 55, CP2 = 75

So, CP1 + CP2 = 1300

55 + 75 = 1300

1 = 10

CP1 = 550, CP2 = 750

questionContent.body:
Ritesh bought 25 washing machines and microwave ovens for Rs. 2,05,000. He sold 80% of the washing machines and 12 microwaves ovens for a profit of Rs 40,000. Each washing machine was marked up by 20% over cost and each microwave oven was sold at a profit of Rs. 2,000. The remaining washing machines and 3 microwave ovens could not be sold. What is Raghav’s overall profit/loss?                                                              

(a) Rs. 1000 profit

(b) Rs. 2500 loss

(c) Rs. 1000 loss

(d) None of these

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details:
Total number of Microwave ovens = 15 (12 sold +3 unsold)

Hence, Washing machines = 10

He sold 12 ovens and 8 washing machines

Hence, In total he sold 80% of both

Thus, He sells 80% of both at a profit of Rs. 40,000.

Cost of 80% of the goods = 0.8*2,05,000 = 1,64,000

Hence, Total SP = 1,64,000+40,000 = 2,04,000

CP = 2,05,000

Loss = Rs.1000

Total SP = 1.4*4725 = 6615

Now, Let the price of 4 seater be x then price of two seater will be .75x.

8x + 22*0.75x = 6615

solution.details:
Candidates passed from institutes Q and R together = [(13% + 17%) of 5700] = 30% of 5700.

Candidates enrolled from institutes Q and R together = [(15% + 10%) of 8550] = 25% of 8550.

Therefore Required Percentage          = [(30% of 5700 / 25% of 8550)         x 100]% = 80%

questionContent.body:
In how many different ways can the letters of the word 'DETAIL' be arranged in such a way that the vowels occupy only the odd positions?

A.     32

B.     48

C.     None of these

D.     60

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Hint    Now, 3 vowels can be placed at any of the three places, marked 1, 3, 5. Number of ways of arranging the vowels = 3P3 = 3! = 6. Also, the 3 consonants can be arranged at the remaining 3 positions. Number of ways of these arrangements = 3P3 = 3! = 6. Total number of ways = (6 x 6) = 36.

questionContent.body: Mukul has earned as an average of 4,200 dollars for the first eleven months of the year. If he justifies his staying in the US on the basis of his ability to earn at least 5000 dollars per month for the entire year, then how much should he earn (in dollars) in the last month to achieve his required average for the whole year?

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: The salary expectation for the whole year is 5000. So, the total earning will be 60000. Earning for 11 months is 4200 so the total earnings are 46200. Now for the last month he has to earn 60000 – 46200 = 13800. 60000

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Sum of x, y and z will be 135. As the average is 45 and Also given that, X-45= 45-Y, X+Y= 90, therefore, 90+Z=135;Z=45

questionContent.body:
The average weight of 39 men travelling to Ladakh is 30. If an obese man with weight 130 kg

join them. What will be the average weight of the people travelling to Ladakh?

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: If the weight of the man would have been 30, then the average weight would have been the same. So, the extra 100 kg that the obese man brings with him would be distributed equally amongst all of them, i.e. 100/40 = 2.5 So, the average becomes 30 + 2.5 = 32.5

questionContent.body: 3 men and 4 women can complete a job in 10 days. 24 men and 2 women can complete it in 2 days. Find the time taken by 11 men and 3 women to complete it.

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Sol: Let the parts of the job done by a man and a woman each day be m units and w units respectively. Given, 3m + 4w = 10 1–––––––– (A) 24m + 2w = 2 1 ––––– (B) Solving for m and w, 100 1 w and 50 1 m = = 11m + 3w = 4 1 ∴ Time taken by 11 men and 3 women to complete the job is 4 days.

solution.details: Sol: Total time for which 18 men work = 240 hours. Number of man hours required to complete the job = (18) (240) man hours. Number of days taken by 15 men working 9 hours a day to complete Use (M1*D1*H1)/W1= (M2*D2*H2)/W2

questionContent.body: A can do a piece of work in 9 days and B in 18 days. They begin together, but A goes away three days before the work is finished. The work lasts for

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Let the work lasts for x days. B works for x days and A works for x – 3 days. ∴ (x-3)/9 + (x/18) = 1 ⇒ x = 8

questionContent.body: A and B together can complete a job in 12 days. A alone can complete it in 24 days. Find the time taken by B to complete it.

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Part of the job that A and B can complete in a day =1/12  Part of the job that A can complete in a day = 1/24  Part of the job that B can complete in a day = 1/12- 1/ 24 = 1/24 ∴ B can complete it in 24 days.

questionContent.body: Ram flew to Lanka in his Pushpak Vahan, at an average speed of 600 km/hr. On his way back along with Sita, because of the heavier baggage that he was carrying, his speed reduced to 400 km/hr. Find the average speed during the journey.

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Explanation: During the journey, Average Speed = 2 × 400 × 600 / (400 + 600)= 480 km /hr.

questionContent.body: A train without stoppages travels at the rate of 50 km per hour and with stoppages travels at the rate of 45 km an hour. How many minutes does the train stop on an average per hour?

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Explanation: Minutes/hr the train stops = (50 -45)/50 x 60 = 5/60 x 60 → 6 min.

questionContent.body: What is the average speed if a man drives 3 hours at 60 km/hr and the next 6 hours at 50 km/hr.?

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details:
Explanation: Average speed =

Total distance/Total time → [(3x60)+(6x50)]/(3+6) = 480/9 =53.33 km/hr

questionContent.body: What is the distance between Alankar’s house and office, if he will reach office late by 20 minutes, traveling at 10 km/hr and will reach early by 15 minutes, traveling at 15 km/hr?

solution.name: Solution 1
solution.details: Explanation: : Difference in timing = 15 – (–20) = 35 min. Let required distance = x. ∴ x/10 - x15 = 35/60 → x = 17.5 km.
